<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900417-0143</DOCNO><DOCID>900417-0143.</DOCID><HL>   Canada to Sell Four Bond Issues</HL><DATE>04/17/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17</SO><CO>   CANDA</CO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)</IN><LP>   OTTAWA -- The Canadian government said it will offer 1.5billion Canadian dollars (US$1.28 billion) of bonds in fourissues this week.   The sale will include 11.75% bonds due Oct. 15, 1993;11.75% bonds due March 1, 1995; 11.50% bonds due Sept. 1,2000; and 11.25% bonds due June 1, 2015. Offering terms areto be announced today.</LP><TEXT>   The Bank of Canada has agreed to purchase at least C$100million of the new bonds. The remainder will be available topublic investors.   Proceeds will be applied toward redemption of C$2.13billion of government bonds maturing May 1 and for generalgovernment purposes, the Finance Department said.</TEXT></DOC>